<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 13 at 5:24PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Warren,
northeastern Hancock, southeastern Greene and Taliaferro Counties
through 600 PM EDT...
At 523 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over White Plains, or 9
miles southeast of Greensboro, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Warrenton, Crawfordville, White Plains, Siloam, Norwood, Sharon,
Camak, Springfield, Cadley, Robinson, Powelton, Barnett, Raytown and
Alexander Stephens Park.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
